japan 's public deficits spawned a national debt of 140 % of annual gdp , without producing any economic resurgence . 
indeed , current budget deficits reflect long-term problems that are not what keynesian theory envisions . 
the debates on deficits must be recast in terms of important intergenerational issues in the long term . 
the problems are subtle , because they depend on the actions of governments to come . 
