still , we need to face firmly to the intergenerational issues at the heart of the economic dilemmas . 
our pension systems and our national budgets must be based on a " generational accounting " which ensures that the economic risk is systematically divided between the generations . 
this means that pension and tax institutions must be designed to take more account of the changing circumstances facing different generations , rather than make fixed promises , which will certainly not be held in any way , some recovery in the future . 
