impose and spend ( please ) 
excessive taxation can blunt incentives and hinder growth . 
but too little taxation can produce the same effects . 
governments with meager tax revenues may not provide basic public goods . 
worse still , low tax revenues in poor countries often result from defects in tax collection systems ( rather than low tax rates ) that also promote not productivity . 
india illustrates the importance of a well-designed tax system . 
in bangalore , high-tech companies have built world-class campuses replete with flawless lawns and high-speed data communication networks . 
outside of these campuses , however , extend open sewers , uncollected garbage , and roads in disrepair . 
while technology companies instantaneously transmit terabytes of data to remote continents , the local transport advance at an almost medieval pace . 
therefore , companies in bangalore run their own bus services , contract with private suppliers for drinking water , and install generators to protect themselves against the power cuts . 
the state can not fix this disaster because it is bankrupt . 
india 's government debt exceeds 70 % of gdp so that more than half of its tax revenues are devoted to paying interest . 
but debt is not the fact of excessive spending in the past . 
india 's government expenditures account for about 15 % of gdp , compared to an average of around 40 % of gdp in the oecd . 
the financial difficulties of india have rather to cause a tax system poorly conceived and badly managed . 
rates and rules for income tax individuals and businesses seem reasonable by international standards . 
however , india 's government collects income taxes amounting to only about 3,7 % of gdp , about half of those in south korea and other asian tigers . 
agriculture in india represents about a quarter of gdp , but even the rich farmers do not pay taxes . 
the export businesses in the software industry and in other industries enjoy tax holidays on their profits , although their employees do pay taxes on their personal incomes . 
despite reasonable rates , tax fraud is commonplace . 
fraud is explained by the fact that the government has not invested in the staff or in the systems to detect tax evaders , which are rarely in prison and who can often get out of paying bribes when they are caught . 
more subtly , the evasion of " direct " taxes on income and profits reflects the mess in the system of " indirect " taxes levied on production and consumption . 
excise taxes account for more than 60 % of india 's indirect taxes , which in turn represent the same proportion of its total tax receipts . 
the basic excise tax has been set at 16 % of the value of the production of a company . 
then there are a variety of cuts , exemptions , and surcharges . 
for example , a " rates of law to conditions " of 8 % is levied on categories like food products , matches , the son of cotton and computers . 
an additional " special excise duty " of 8 % is levied on products that include polyester strands , cars , air conditioners and tires . 
an " additional excise duty " ( not to be confused with the " special excise duty " ) is levied on " products of special importance . " 
exemptions from excise taxes are numerous and complex , including the companies with total annual revenues of less than 10 million rupees and businesses located in certain troubled or backward areas . 
in general , the exemptions fall in 70 major categories , subdivided into 259 entries , 52 conditions and 7 lists , each containing many elements . 
exemptions invite abuse . 
for a certain sum , officials located at the bottom of the hierarchy , who have considerable discretion in the application of conditions , can be persuaded to give favorable interpretations . 
the products taxed at high rates ( for example , polished granite ) are sold as products taxed at lower rates ( for example , as unpolished granite ) . 
fraud of excise taxes is more contagious than tax fraud on profits and incomes . 
if a company fraud excise duty and the tax rate is high compared to pre-tax profit margins in the industry , its competitors also have to cheat , just to be able to survive . 
while the fraud increases , governments levy of rights " additional " or " special " incite greater fraud . 
perceptions of direct taxes also suffer . 
the bribe paid to the excise tax for a favorable classification , the difference between the value of polished and unpolished granite , and the omission of true revenues create " black " funds , which cannot be declared on income-tax returns . 
in addition to weaken the ability of the state to provide essential public goods , schemes to escape indirect taxes also discourage businesses to adopt more productive technologies , which requires technologies involving a large-scale deployment . 
