the debate , in germany , is still largely a policy debate . 
when the opposition offers the government negotiate the reform of social protection or , more recently , to combat unemployment , the underlying challenge is not posed in terms competence rather than values . 
yet , in the fields of political debate english or german , or elsewhere in europe , the clash of values threaten . 
the parties are fighting for those who can " feel comfortable in their own place " , but they may not fully realize that this is only partly a matter of policy . 
religion will never be an important factor in european politics : opinion polls show that the religious practice remains one of the few major differences between the americans and europeans . 
