the second lesson is that countries need to plan their budgets depending on the rising fiscal costs by an ageing population . 
long-term budgetary conditions are rarely taken into account by taxpayers or parliament . 
governments should be required to submit long-term budget assessments at the same time their annual budget proposals , in order to reduce the tendency towards short-run political manipulation of the budget . 
