first of all , the question of research . 
europe is lagging behind the us in every field : the number of patents , the number of nobel laureates , the number of researchers from other countries that it can draw . 
but the funding is only part of the problem . 
a euro spent on research in europe is less productive than a dollar spent in the us , and for two reasons : the motives and the demand for technology . 
we fear that additional spending not followed by a change of archaic university rules only serve to produce more waste , not more of discoveries . 
it would only increase the power , prestige and the resources of entrenched lobbies of established university professors who often prevent access and competition in their university . 
the demand for technology also plays an important role . 
