cell phones , satellite tracking and high-resolution cameras are expensive , but fortunately for the industries that use them , their development costs have been partly borne by the government . 
one of the main reasons for the superiority of the us in research is the importance and the composition of defense expenditure . 
the pentagon 's budget is not only important : it represents more than half of all us government spending on research and development ; in france , defense spending is only around a quarter of the total . 
in 1999 , us spending on research and development related to the defence have reached 0,45 % of gdp , top of the uk and france , which have reached only half of that figure , with 0,26 % and 0,22 % , respectively . 
