prime minister ariel sharon 's announcement showing its willingness to dismantle jewish settlements in the gaza strip , as well as some settlements in the west bank , has shocked and wrong-footed the nation of israel and the nations of the world . 
many have denounced sharon 's plan as a trick . 
but this surprise was crazy since the beginning . 
despite the appearance that they give to foreigners , the debates in israel on the future of the occupied territories have never been reduced to a simple story of hawks and doves . 
like any thing in israel , the process is more complex , and particularly when the hawks are concerned . 
overall , there are two species of israeli hawks : the ideological and the strategic . 
ideological hawks view the occupied territories as an integral part of the historical land of israel , the homeland of the jewish people . 
for them , the territories are part of the jewish heritage , which explains their insistence to call on the west bank by its historic designation hebrew : judea and samaria . 
not all ideological hawks are religious , although those who are base their claim on divine promises and prophecies . 
but a lot of ideological hawks are secular nationalists , and their jargon is similar to that of the nationalists types of eastern europe and central europe . 
the former prime minister menachem begin and yitzhak shamir belonged to this category . 
ideological hawks usually come from the national party religious and the likud . 
they are inspired by the nationalist ideology associated with vladimir jabotinsky , who founded " revisionist " zionism in order to challenge the more moderate version passed by the founding fathers of israel , like chaim weizmann and david ben-gurion . 
then there are the strategic hawks . 
for them , given the narrow and vulnerable geographic shape israel and continuing arab enmity , control of the west bank and gaza is not an ideological imperative , but responds to security considerations . 
for them , jewish settlements in the occupied territories are not a return to historical lands , but security outposts , aimed at preventing ( or push for a place more strategic ) an attack at the heart of israel . 
this assessment of the situation may be right or wrong , but it is certainly not ideological . 
ariel sharon , who comes from a military background ( he grew up in a social environment which ideas much the labour party than jabotinsky ) , is a strategic hawk . 
for ideological hawks , the compromises are a betrayal : how jeopardising the historical heritage of the jewish people , not to mention god 's promise to abraham ? 
strategic hawks , however , are open to negotiations and the compromises practices , if the circumstances are right and if the security considerations justify it in their eyes . 
it is in this context that must be considered the measures taken by sharon . 
he was elected on the promise that he would bring peace and security . 
he has brought neither . 
with the defeat and the disappearance of saddam hussein , the danger of a " eastern front " against israel has weakened . 
without a palestinian partner , and due to continuing palestinian terrorism that the actions of israel 's fierce fail to quell the measures taken by sharon derive from this reflection geared towards the strategy : set up an effective barrier , move some of the isolated and strategically untenable settlements , and wait . 
the statements of sharon during the previous year seem to follow a model well defined . 
first , he admitted that " a day or two , " a palestinian state would emerge , an idea unthinkable for dyed-in-the-wool ideological hawks . 
a few months later , he scandalized his own likud party conference by stating that the occupation was unacceptable and unsustainable , another shock to those who had always talked of " liberated " rather than " occupied " territories . 
last december , he has explicitly stated that israel was geared towards a unilateral ceasefire which would lead to the " relocation " of some settlements . 
although this was still in a simple verbiage , they have still been a new language for a likud prime minister . 
sharon 's latest statements yet explicitly named the settlements to be evacuated ; the director of the national security council , general giora eiland , has been appointed president of an inter-ministerial relocation committee to draw up plans to evacuate the settlements and compensation for the settlers relocated . 
all of this has radically altered israel 's domestic political map . 
some ideological hawks in sharon 's government have threatened to resign ; shimon peres has announced that the labour party will offer sharon a parliamentary safety net ; there is also a question that the labour party to join a national unity government . 
the test , of course , is not planning , but the implementation of withdrawal , and the road is long and bumpy . 
sharon 's timing may have been guided by the problems with police investigations on its alleged corruption . 
however , anyone who would like to predict sharon 's future behavior should bear in mind that unlike begin and shamir , sharon has the military , and for him , security , and not the ideology , come first . 
his apparent pragmatism should come as no surprise . 
