héma-québec yesterday celebrated the 10th anniversary of its foundation , and its president , the dre francine décary , had reason to celebrate , because héma-québec has become one of the suppliers of blood the more security and efficient in the world . 
and above all , he has regained the confidence of the public who had been seriously dented by the contaminated blood scandal in the 1980s and 1990s . 
as you know , the reserves managed by the national blood transfusion service of the canadian red cross have been infected by the acquired immunodeficiency virus ( hiv ) and hepatitis c virus during the 1980s . 
before this tragedy and the grumbles of the public , the government of canada has established in february 1994 a public inquiry , chaired by judge krever giant , which was intended to shed light on the circumstances that led to such a tragedy and to make recommendations for such a calamity never happens again . 
while the judge krever belatedly to submit his report , some provinces were then set up a committee to plan a new management system of the blood in canada . 
in quebec , the committee gélineau has fulfilled this mandate . 
following the reports gélineau and krever , two suppliers have been created in canada : héma-québec to serve the quebec and the canadian company of blood to supply all the other provinces and the two territories . 
" in 1998 , when héma-québec began its activities , only 38 % of people still had confidence in the system of blood in quebec , recalls the dre décary . 
the situation was discouraging . 
to force of efforts to improve the safety of blood products and work on the ground during the years that followed , we have regained the confidence of the public , " she said before proudly say that at the beginning of 2008 , nearly 94 % of the population québécoise was now confidence in héma-québec . 
the dre décary warned however that " confidence is something extremely fragile . " 
from its inception , the 28 september 1998 héma-québec has applied the precautionary principle . 
at that time , it was in europe to the emergence of many cases of the human form of mad cow disease , a new variant cjd , tells the one which takes the strong since its foundation in 1998 . 
" and we do not know whether the disease could be transmitted by blood . 
we then relied on one of the main recommendations of the reports krever and gélineau , that when we do not know , and that a serious disease can be arranged , creutzfeldt-jakob disease , which is characterised by a degeneration of the brain , leading inevitably to the death , we undertake measures of exclusion . 
in april 1999 , we therefore refused the blood of people who had stayed more than a month in the uk since 1980 . 
however , a few years ago , it has been proven beyond all doubt that this disease is transmitted by blood . 
this episode we thus showed that the precautionary principle that has been applied made sense . " 
in 1999 , appeared on the market a technique is much more sensitive hiv testing : the tests of nucleic acid ( tan ) that detect directly in the blood of donors the presence of the virus itself , and not that of antibodies against the virus , which rested the tests used until then . 
the tan have helped to shorten the period silent , which stretches between the moment where the person has been infected and the one where the first virus can be detected in the blood by our technical , explains the specialist . 
we were able to reduce this period to a period of less than a week . 
it has also decreased substantially the risk that some donors are infected without knowing it , and that we can detect . 
these improvements have enabled us to significantly reduce the risk of contracting aids from a blood transfusion . 
today , one in 12 million runs the risk of receiving blood contaminated with hiv . 
" in other words , this means that it will distribute 12 million blood products before someone is infected with hiv . 
as héma-québec distributes each year between 400 and 500 000 000 blood products , it will take more than 24 years before a case of hiv transmission by a blood products . 
