75 % of working mothers have had problems professionals because of their maternity 
discrimination at work has increased in recent years , especially for women of young people who want to be mothers . 
it is this that reveals the study " fertility and career women in spain , " carried out by the csic in collaboration with the instituto the mujer . 
the inquiry , carried out on 9 737 women of 15 to 75 years , leaves no room for doubt : 75 % of working mothers have seen their career limited because of motherhood . 
the study indicates that there are many differences on the beginning of life as a couple , and the number of children , if the woman is working or not , and the type of employment occupied . 
those who have not of activity outside the home , work part-time work or have a little stable , are earlier in couple , have their first pregnancy sooner and have more children . 
however , women who have a stable job , mainly in the public sector , postpone the entry in life as a couple , and the first pregnancy , and have fewer children . 
women between 35 and 49 years with a fixed work have their first child , on average , 3,7 years after being installed as couples . this figure rises to 4,1 among those who work in the public sector . " these data show that women who have a stable job had need more time in their lives to get it , which has led to the postponement of the union and the arrival of the children . 
in addition , the type of employment exercised influence largely motherhood , but less the starting date of common life , " explains the researcher of csic margarita delgado . 
the level of studies is another factor that widening the gap of the age of marriage of women and their first child . 
according to the survey , the higher the level of training is high , the more they marry and have their first child later . 
the difference is also maintains among women of the same generation . 
for example , in the group have between 35 and 49 years , those who have made studies basic and higher respectively have been mothers for the first time to 25,1 and 32,1 years on average . 
" another disctinction also appears between women , depending on their level of studies . 
while those who have done the basic studies marry and have their first child before finding a stable job , those who have done studies of average level or above reverse this programme and give priority to obtaining a stable work as a precondition to marriage and the arrival of a child , " says mrs delgado . 
