the emergency braking is now obligatory 
as has occurred with the system anti-lock brakes abs and , as this will take place with the esp stability control , the braking systems of emergency will be a mandatory part on european cars . 
they are already mandatory in cars of tourism and light commercial vehicles , while newly registered for the rest of the vehicles a period of deficiency has been set until the end of february 2011 . 
the measure , imposed by the european union , is intended to strengthen the protection of pedestrians , even if , by his mode of action , it can also help prevent many rear shocks . 
the assistant emergency braking is increasing the pressure on the brakes in emergency cases detected by the system through kicked given by the driver . 
but it does not always keeps the pressure until the end . 
according to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars bosch , a third of the drivers involved in an accident had not been able to rely on the brake before the collision , and half of them had not benefited from its full force . 
